{"quote": "Recognizing Your Archenemy", "page_title": "Chuck Klosterman", "page_bio": "Chuck Klosterman (born June 5, 1972) is an American pop-culture journalist, critic, and essayist. Klosterman is currently a columnist for Esquire and has written for GQ, SPIN, The Washington Post, The Believer, ESPN and The New York Times Magazine. He is also the author of six books (Fargo Rock City - Killing Yourself to Live - Chuck Klosterman IV - Sex, Drugs and Cocoa Puffs - Downtown Owl - Eating The Dinosaur).", "page_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chuck Klosterman"}